VALUES
(44, 7, 42, 18, 31, 26, 28, 'worship the host of heaven', 'Worship of Heavenly Bodies', 'This connection highlights the theme of worshiping celestial bodies. Both passages address the consequences of turning away from God to worship the sun and moon, emphasizing the iniquity of such actions.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 42, 23, 63, 10, 10, 'gave them up to worship', 'Rebellion and Divine Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of Israel''s rebellion against God and His subsequent response. Both passages illustrate how Israel''s actions led to divine abandonment and conflict.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 30, 5, 26, 27, 'tabernacle of Moloch', 'Connection of Moloch and Captivity', 'Both passages emphasize the worship of Moloch and the consequences of idolatry, specifically mentioning captivity as a result. The phrases regarding the tabernacle of Moloch and the imagery of captivity beyond Babylon or Damascus create a direct thematic link.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 2, 20, 4, 5, 'the tabernacle of Moloch', 'Idolatry and Divine Jealousy', 'This connection highlights the theme of idolatry, as both passages address the worship of false gods and the consequences of such actions. Acts 7:43 mentions the worship of Moloch and Remphan, while Exodus 20:4-5 explicitly forbids the making of graven images and warns of God''s jealousy.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 5, 5, 8, 9, 'the tabernacle of Moloch', 'Connection of Idolatry and Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the prohibition of making graven images and the worship of false gods. Acts 7:43 references the worship of Moloch and Remphan, which aligns with Deuteronomy 5:8-9''s command against serving idols.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 3, 20, 2, 5, 'tabernacle of Moloch', 'Connection of Moloch Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the worship of Moloch and the severe consequences for such actions. Acts 7:43 references the taking up of the tabernacle of Moloch, while Leviticus 20:2-5 outlines the punishment for giving seed to Molech.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 5, 4, 16, 18, 'figures which ye made to worship them', 'Idolatry and Graven Images', 'This connection highlights the theme of idolatry, as both passages warn against the creation and worship of images. Acts 7:43 mentions figures made for worship, paralleling Deuteronomy 4:16-18''s prohibition against making graven images.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 12, 17, 16, 18, 'worship them', 'Worship of False Gods', 'Both passages emphasize the worship of false gods, specifically mentioning practices that provoke the Lord''s anger. Acts 7:43 refers to the worship of Moloch and Remphan, while 2 Kings 17:16-18 describes the worship of molten images and Baal, highlighting a common theme of idolatry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 43, 12, 18, 11, 11, 'carry you away beyond Babylon', 'Exile and Idolatry Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of exile resulting from idolatry. Both passages reference the consequences of turning away from God, leading to the Israelites'' removal from their land.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 2, 25, 40, 40, 'according to the fashion that he had seen', 'Connection of Divine Instruction', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of following God''s specific instructions for the tabernacle. Acts 7:44 refers to Moses making it ''according to the fashion'' shown to him, paralleling Exodus 25:40''s directive to make it ''after their pattern.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 2, 38, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Tabernacle References', 'Both passages emphasize the tabernacle of testimony, highlighting its significance in the wilderness and its construction according to divine command. This connection illustrates the continuity of God''s instructions to Moses regarding the tabernacle.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 58, 8, 5, 5, 'according to the fashion that he had seen', 'Connection of Tabernacle Instructions', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of making the tabernacle according to a divine pattern. Acts 7:44 mentions Moses receiving instructions, while Hebrews 8:5 highlights the necessity of adhering to the pattern shown to him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 4, 1, 50, 53, 'tabernacle of witness', 'Connection of the Tabernacle''s Role', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the tabernacle in the wilderness. Acts 7:44 refers to the tabernacle of witness, while Numbers 1:50-53 details the Levites'' responsibilities regarding the tabernacle of testimony.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 4, 9, 15, 15, 'tabernacle of witness', 'Connection of the Tabernacle', 'Both passages emphasize the tabernacle as a significant structure in the wilderness. Acts 7:44 refers to it as the ''tabernacle of witness,'' while Numbers 9:15 describes it as the ''tent of the testimony,'' highlighting its importance in the Israelite journey.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 6, 18, 1, 1, 'tabernacle of witness in the wilderness', 'Connection of the Tabernacle', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the tabernacle in the journey of the Israelites. Acts 7:44 refers to the tabernacle in the wilderness, while Joshua 18:1 describes its establishment at Shiloh, indicating its central role in Israel''s worship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 44, 13, 28, 11, 11, 'according to the fashion that he had seen', 'Patterns of Divine Instruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine instruction regarding sacred structures. Both passages emphasize the importance of following specific patterns as given by God, first to Moses for the tabernacle and then to Solomon for the temple.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 19, 44, 2, 2, 'whom God drave out before the face', 'Divine Action Against Nations', 'This connection highlights God''s active role in driving out nations. Both passages emphasize the theme of God removing the heathen and establishing His people in their place.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 6, 18, 1, 1, 'brought in with Jesus into the possession', 'Connection of Land and Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of the Israelites'' possession of land, as seen in both passages. Acts 7:45 refers to the land brought in with Jesus, paralleling Joshua 18:1 where the tabernacle is set up in subdued land.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 6, 23, 9, 9, 'whom God drave out before the face', 'Divine Conquest of Nations', 'This connection highlights God''s role in driving out nations before His people. Both passages emphasize the theme of divine assistance in conquering strong nations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 5, 32, 49, 49, 'possession of the Gentiles', 'Possession of the Land', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God giving the land as a possession to His people. Acts 7:45 refers to the possession brought in by the fathers, while Deuteronomy 32:49 speaks of the land of Canaan given to the children of Israel for a possession.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 7, 18, 31, 31, NULL, 'Connection of Idolatry and Worship', 'This connection highlights the theme of idolatry in Israel''s history. Both passages reference the actions of the Israelites in relation to their worship practices, particularly in the context of the land they possessed.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 9, 4, 4, 4, 'brought in with Jesus into the possession', 'Connection of the Ark and Possession', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the ark of the covenant in relation to God''s presence among His people. Acts 7:45 references the ark being brought into the possession of the Gentiles, while 1 Samuel 4:4 describes the ark''s location with Eli''s sons, highlighting its importance in Israel''s history.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 45, 10, 6, 1, 23, 'brought in with Jesus into the possession of the Gentiles', 'David and the Ark of God', 'This connection highlights the significance of the ark of God in both passages. In Acts 7:45, the ark is mentioned as being brought into the possession of the Gentiles, while 2 Samuel 6:1-23 describes David''s efforts to bring the ark to Jerusalem, emphasizing its central role in Israel''s worship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 19, 132, 1, 5, 'the God of Jacob', 'Connection of David''s Desire', 'Both passages emphasize David''s desire to find a dwelling for God, specifically referencing ''the God of Jacob.'' This connection highlights David''s commitment to establishing a place for divine worship.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 44, 13, 22, 22, 'found favour before God', 'Connection Between David and Favor', 'Both passages emphasize God''s favor towards David. Acts 7:46 mentions finding favor before God, while Acts 13:22 highlights David as a man after God''s own heart.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 10, 7, 1, 5, 'desired to find a tabernacle', 'David''s Desire for a Temple', 'Both passages emphasize David''s desire to build a dwelling for God. Acts 7:46 references finding favor with God, which aligns with David''s intention in 2 Samuel 7:1-5 to construct a house for the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 9, 16, 1, 1, 'found favour before God', 'Connection of Divine Favor', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine selection and favor. In Acts, the reference to finding favor before God relates to God''s choice of David, as noted in 1 Samuel, where God directs Samuel to anoint a new king.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 9, 16, 11, 13, 'found favour before God', 'Connection of Favor and Anointing', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine favor as seen in both passages. In Acts 7:46, the favor before God is linked to the desire for a tabernacle, while in 1 Samuel 16:11-13, David is chosen and anointed by God, indicating his favor.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 10, 6, 21, 21, 'found favour before God', 'Divine Favor and Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine favor in both passages. In Acts 7:46, the focus is on finding favor before God, while in 2 Samuel 6:21, David acknowledges God''s choice of him as ruler, emphasizing his relationship with the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 46, 13, 17, 1, 4, 'desired to find a tabernacle', 'David''s Desire for a Tabernacle', 'Both passages emphasize David''s desire to build a dwelling for God. Acts 7:46 mentions finding favor to create a tabernacle, while 1 Chronicles 17:1-4 describes David''s intention to build a house for the ark of the covenant.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
